# Transcribed from cf13_6.main.cpp. The driver interleaves 3 dumps (a
# bound probe chk_b over 0..5 plus a cursor scan all_f); the mid-run
# cross-support state (t(2) surviving via b after a removes 2) is only
# visible in that interleaved output — only the final state is checked
# here.

batch
+ a 1
+ a 2
end

batch
+ b 2
+ b 3
end

# t(2) still supported via b.
batch
- a 2
end

# t = {1, 4}.
batch
+ b 4
- b 2
- b 3
end
